GLOBAL INTEGRATION REFACTOR (INTEGRATE_HARMONYPY) - ✅ COMPLETED (March 02, 2026)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Scope completed in this sprint:
  ✅ Replaced per-sample integration path with global multi-sample integration process
  ✅ Added new process INTEGRATE_HARMONYPY (merge → Harmony → integrated.h5ad)
  ✅ DGE now runs on integrated object when run_integration=true
  ✅ Added integrated sample split outputs (integrated/samples/*_integrated.h5ad)
  ✅ Dashboard default data auto-detection now prioritizes integrated/integrated.h5ad
  ✅ Fixed runtime stability issues discovered in SLURM execution

Implemented details:
  ✔ PIPELINE #1: New global integration module
    - New module: modules/local/integrate_harmonypy.nf
    - New helper script: bin/split_integrated_by_sample.py
    - Published outputs:
      * integrated/integrated.h5ad
      * integrated/samples/*_integrated.h5ad
      * integrated/integration_results/*

  ✔ PIPELINE #2: Workflow refactor
    - workflows/scannex.nf now routes multi-sample annotated objects into INTEGRATE_HARMONYPY
    - DGE input uses integrated.h5ad when integration is enabled
    - Legacy merge path is kept only when integration is disabled

  ✔ STABILITY #1: Integration runtime fixes
    - normalize_integrate.py hardened for Harmony output shape compatibility
    - Added direct harmonypy fallback when scanpy wrapper fails on shape assignment
    - Fixed LISI naming collision causing: 'bool' object is not callable

  ✔ STABILITY #2: Nextflow runtime fixes
    - Fixed missing split script in process work directory by passing script as process input
    - Removed unnecessary .first() usage on value channels in workflow
    - Removed stale process selectors in modules.config to reduce warning noise

